The paper deals with deep hashing, which is a technique used for image retrieval. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of quantization loss, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL) research.
